BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Community Events,Performances,Student Life
DESCRIPTION:This Heels masterclass begins with a grounding\, yoga-inspired\
 , and somatic warm-up to help you drop into your body\, breathe deeply\, an
 d cultivate presence and find strength. From there\, we’ll move into playfu
 l\, beginner-friendly choreography and across the floor exercises in heels\
 , exploring movement practices designed to awaken your sensuality and confi
 dence. We will dive into a group choreography session toward the end of cla
 ss. This is a space to move with intention\, embody authenticity\, and conn
 ect with your body in a way that feels bold\, beautiful\, and free. It is r
 ecommended to bring the following: a journal for reflections\, dancing heel
 s you feel confident and comfortable in\, and a water bottle. \n\n \n\nArti
 st Bio: Anabelle Scarborough is a dancer\, choreographer\, educator\, and v
 isual artist based on the East Coast\, currently based in the Raleigh–Durha
 m region of North Carolina. Raised in the Appalachian Mountains\, her work 
 is deeply informed by themes of beauty\, femininity\, spontaneity\, improvi
 sation\, and community. She trained at the Martha Graham School in New York
  City and at UNC Chapel Hill\, studying modern\, contemporary\, improvisati
 on\, composition\, ballet\, and heels. She is a 200-hour certified yoga ins
 tructor through the Asheville Yoga Center and is currently pursuing a Maste
 r’s degree in Clinical Mental Health Counseling at Wake Forest University. 
 Together\, these experiences inform a holistic\, trauma-informed approach t
 o movement that honors both emotional and physical wellbeing. Anabelle is c
 urrently a Guest Teaching Artist at North Carolina State University's Depar
 tment of Performing Arts and Technology. Working at the intersection of art
 \, healing\, and community\, Anabelle’s interdisciplinary practice spans da
 nce\, yoga\, photography\, film\, and arts-based education. \n\nHer project
 s reimagine how performance can activate and transform shared spaces\, invi
 ting audiences into intimate\, participatory experiences that emphasize pre
 sence\, connection\, and collective storytelling. More can be found here: A
 nabellescarborough.com
DTEND:20260226T234500Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025710Z
DTSTART:20260226T223000Z
GEO:35.783875;-78.673114
LOCATION:Wellness and Recreation Center and Carmichael Gym\, 2307
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Heels Master Class with Anabelle Scarborough
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52082298673331
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/heels-master-class-with-anabelle-scarbo
 rough
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Training
DESCRIPTION:NC State Innovation and Entrepreneurship has developed an incub
 ator program to support early-stage startups. During the incubator\, studen
 ts will work on furthering their concepts through a variety of fundamental 
 practices\, such as doing customer discovery\, exploring business modeling 
 and thinking through commercialization strategy. This friendly\, low-stakes
  and informal cohort is the perfect place to bounce ideas off one another a
 nd hold one another accountable for tangible next steps for your new ventur
 e.\n\nThe incubator occurs over a rolling 10-week period\, with entrepreneu
 rs joining on a drop-in basis. Student entrepreneurs are also eligible for 
 micro funding. Funding can range from roughly $200 to $800 per student (up 
 to $1\,000 per team)\, depending on your venture and its needs.\n\nWhile th
 e cohort will meet for two hours every other week\, the program gives stude
 nts access to an asynchronous library of resources they can navigate at the
 ir own pace. Throughout the incubator period\, participants will also be co
 nnected to mentorship and other forms of support. Every other week’s sessio
 n will kick off with founder updates\, including what’s working\, roadblock
 s and goals for the week.\n\nFor more information about Launchpad and to ap
 ply\, please visit the Launchpad web page.\n\nThe spring 2026 LaunchPad sch
 edule and topics are below. Dates are subject to change.\n\nJan. 29: Intros
  and expectationsFeb. 12: Pivoting and deployment of your product/service i
 n the face of extreme challengesFeb. 26: Customer discovery/market fitMarch
  12: Short-form video content marketingMarch 26: Product scaling\, producti
 on and crowdfundingApril 9: To be determinedApril 23: To be determined
DTEND:20260227T003000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025710Z
DTSTART:20260226T223000Z
GEO:35.771067;-78.676515
LOCATION:Partners I – NC State University\, Albright Entrepreneurship Garag
 e Classroom
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:LaunchPad Incubator
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51939248622114
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/launchpad-incubator
END:VEVENT
