BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Lectures and Talks,Community Events
DESCRIPTION:As the Baby Boomer generation enters retirement at a record pac
 e\, the traditional isolated model of senior housing is being reimagined. T
 he future of the urban environment belongs to intergenerational living — co
 mmunities designed to foster connection across all ages rather than silos.\
 n\nJoin the Pappas Real Estate Development Program for "Designing for Every
  Age: New Models in Senior Living\," the next installment of the Placemakin
 g by Design speaker series. You’ll hear from Avi Grewal\, Thad Moore and Im
 ran Aukhil on the innovations reshaping senior living and real estate devel
 opment. This event is free for everyone. Let us know that you're planning t
 o attend by registering.\n\nThe discussion will be held Friday\, March 6\, 
 from 9 to 10:30 a.m. at Raleigh Founded cafe\, which is inside Partners Bui
 lding I on Centennial Campus. Free parking is available at the Oval West Pa
 rking Deck\, directly behind the Partners Building I. You can validate your
  license plate when you arrive.
DTEND:20260306T153000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025711Z
DTSTART:20260306T140000Z
GEO:35.771067;-78.676515
LOCATION:Partners I – NC State University\, Raleigh Founded
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Designing for Every Age: New Models in Senior Living
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52205468556834
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/placemaking-by-design-designing-for-eve
 ry-age-new-models-in-senior-living
END:VEVENT
