BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Lectures and Talks,Exhibitions
DESCRIPTION:In celebration of the 50th anniversary of NC State’s Department
  of Communication\, join the department for the Alumni Media Arts Showcase\
 , which will feature a panel of alumni discussing their experiences in film
 \, television and digital media. The showcase will also be an opportunity f
 or students to engage with the alumni as they share their creative and tech
 nical expertise. Here are the panelists:\n\nPaul Bonesteel ’87 is an indepe
 ndent documentary filmmaker and founder of Bonesteel Films in Asheville. He
  is the director of The George Masa Story\, The Mystery of George Masa and 
 other acclaimed historical films.Davy Nethercutt ’91 is a visual effects su
 pervisor with over 25 years in film and television. Nethercutt's credits in
 clude Star Trek: Deep Space Nine\, X-Men and numerous commercial projects.T
 im Kiernan ’02 is a creative director at 521 Studios. Kiernan leads a multi
 disciplinary team that develops branded content and storytelling for corpor
 ate and nonprofit clients across the Southeast.Daniel Gallagher '13 is a ch
 aracter artist and animator whose credits include Fox Sports and FX's Legio
 n. Gallagher is known for blending visual storytelling and digital design i
 n large-scale productions.Mattison Domke-Latz '20\, a multimedia strategist
  at the NC State University Libraries\, focuses on content development\, di
 gital communications and public engagement through creative media.
DTEND:20260306T170000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025711Z
DTSTART:20260306T150000Z
GEO:35.787562;-78.669711
LOCATION:D.H. Hill Jr. Library\, North Forum
SEQUENCE:0
