BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Community Events
DESCRIPTION:In celebration of the enduring legacy of the annual NC State Po
 wwow\, join the NC State University Libraries for a special immersive showc
 ase featuring the university’s own student drum group\, Miskw’a Waya. Since
  its inception in 1990\, the Powwow has served as a cultural cornerstone an
 d a family reunion for the eight state-recognized tribes of North Carolina 
 and Indigenous nations across the country. This event offers a rare opportu
 nity to experience that history through the sights and sounds of the 360 Cy
 ma Rubin Visualization Gallery.\n\nAlways a profound sensory experience\, t
 he exhibit and drum group performance provide an intimate look at the creat
 ive and spiritual processes behind the music that anchors the Native studen
 t experience on ancestral lands. During this live showcase\, we will hear t
 he powerful songs of Miskw’a Waya and explore the heartbeat of the drum thr
 ough a 360-degree digital retrospective of the Powwow's most moving moments
  over the decades.
DTEND:20260309T220000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025711Z
DTSTART:20260309T210000Z
GEO:35.787562;-78.669711
LOCATION:D.H. Hill Jr. Library\, Cyma Rubin Visualization
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:A Story of the NC State Powwow and Performance
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52273192875640
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/vision-of-the-arena-a-story-of-the-nc-s
 tate-powwow-and-performance
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Student Life
DESCRIPTION:Join the Adopted Students Union for Roots and Routes\, a March 
 9 event that will be all about reflection and reconnection. We encourage pa
 rticipants to fully embrace where they came from and to create a visual or 
 mood board that offers a glimpse into who they are and what represents thei
 r “lost culture.” The goal is to foster a judgment-free space where everyon
 e feels comfortable expressing themselves and reconnecting with parts of th
 eir identity. Please create a physical or digital visual/mood board before 
 our March 9 event. During the event\, you can share your board. If you'd ju
 st like to visit and connect with others without creating a mood board\, yo
 u can do so as well.\n\nFree snacks will be provided. With St. Patrick’s Da
 y right around the corner\, you’ll also get to build your own “luck bag" an
 d decorate it with markers and other craft supplies.
DTEND:20260310T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025711Z
DTSTART:20260309T220000Z
GEO:35.787631;-78.672608
LOCATION:Fox Science Teaching Laboratory\, 306
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Roots and Routes
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52240846250152
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/roots-routes
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Lectures and Talks,Community Events
DESCRIPTION:Solving Sustainability is a live interdisciplinary podcast that
  seeks to raise awareness about macro-level sustainability challenges and i
 nnovations while fostering meaningful discussion between students\, researc
 hers\, entrepreneurs and policymakers.\n\nThe third episode of the podcast\
 , "Future Sources of Protein\," will delve into the scientific innovations\
 , environmental trade-offs and economic considerations shaping alternative 
 protein systems. The discussion will focus on plant-based foods\, precision
  fermentation and cultivated meat and how they will shape the future of sus
 tainable food production. The guests on the podcast will be: \n\nRohan Shir
 waiker\, co-director of the Bezos CenterRody Hawkins\, CEO of Improved Natu
 reAjinkya Arun Atkare\, co-president of the Alt Protein Project at NC State
DTEND:20260309T233000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025711Z
DTSTART:20260309T220000Z
GEO:35.771067;-78.676515
LOCATION:Partners I – NC State University\, Raleigh Founded (Suite 1650)
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Solving Sustainability Live Podcast: Future of Protein
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52081491983011
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/solving-sustainability-live-podcast-ai-
 and-sustainability
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Lectures and Talks
DESCRIPTION:In celebration of Women’s History Month\, join NC State Univers
 ity Libraries for a conversation with Amy Rossi about her debut novel\, The
  Cover Girl. Janine Kossen\, JD\, MPH\, director of NC State’s Women’s Cent
 er\, will moderate the conversation.\n\nInspired by true events and told in
  two timelines\, Rossi's novel explores the life of Birdie Rhodes\, a teena
 ge girl who becomes a model in the 1970s and gets entangled with an older r
 ock star who becomes her guardian. The story follows Birdie's life from her
  discovery at 13 through her traumatic relationship with the musician and h
 er quiet life decades later. Rossi is the director of development communica
 tions at NC State. You can read more about her writing journey in the NC St
 ate Magazine.
DTEND:20260309T233000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025711Z
DTSTART:20260309T223000Z
GEO:35.787562;-78.669711
LOCATION:D.H. Hill Jr. Library\, Fishbowl Forum
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Author Conversation With Amy Rossi
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51751171999892
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/author-conversation-with-amy-rossi-the-
 cover-girl
END:VEVENT
