BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Lectures and Talks
DESCRIPTION:Will AI allow us to communicate — really communicate — with our
  pets in the future? Will genetic tools allow us to prevent and cure diseas
 es or bring beloved companions back to life through cloning? What will be t
 he nature of our relationships with our pets\, and what do we hope it will 
 be? Join us to explore these and other questions with a panel of experts:\n
 \nCarlos Goller is a teaching professor in biological sciences. He studies 
 molecular microbiology\, metagenomics and other topics relevant to the futu
 re of pets.Margaret Gruen is an associate professor of behavioral medicine 
 at NC State’s College of Veterinary Medicine\, a principal investigator for
  the Thinking Pets Program and former co-director of Duke Canine Cognition 
 Center.Alper Bozkurt is the founder and director of the Integrated Bionic M
 icroSystems Laboratory at NC State\, where his team explores novel bionic i
 nterfaces with cockroaches\, sphinx moths\, plants\, mussels\, birds\, cani
 nes\, horses\, lemurs and humans.Meredith Spence Beaulieu\, a medical and v
 eterinary entomologist and program manager for the Global One Health Academ
 y\, will facilitate the conversation to consider current issues and opportu
 nities related to the future of pets.\n\nBefore the panel discussion\, stop
  by for Pause for Paws to check out the NC State University Libraries’ robo
 tic therapy pets and to learn about sensor technology that can monitor and 
 improve pet health.\n\nThe “Hopeful Futures” series is part of the Long Vie
 w Project and is co-sponsored by the Libraries\, the Office of University I
 nterdisciplinary Programs\, the Global One Health Academy and Wicked Proble
 ms\, Wolfpack Solutions.
DTEND:20260311T214500Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025711Z
DTSTART:20260311T203000Z
GEO:35.787562;-78.669711
LOCATION:D.H. Hill Jr. Library\, Fishbowl Forum
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Hopeful Futures: Future of Pets
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51751172022423
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/hopeful-futures-future-of-pets
END:VEVENT
