BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Meetings and Conferences
DESCRIPTION:Join academic and industry leaders for a one-day conference at 
 NC State’s campus (or remotely) exploring how artificial intelligence can i
 mpact biopharmaceutical and biomanufacturing for transformative changes in 
 process efficiency\, process effectiveness\, sustainability\, adaptiveness 
 and flexibility.\n\nConference Details\n\nDate: Thursday\, March 12\, 2026\
 n(Due to inclement weather\, the original date of January 26\, 2026 has bee
 n postponed to the date listed above.)Time: 8 a.m. to 6 p.m.Location: Duke 
 Energy Hall\, Hunt Library\, NC State UniversityAim: Discuss the potential 
 and challenges of practical applications to innovate in biomanufacturing op
 erationsFormat: Hybrid (in-person and online attendance options)The confere
 nce is open to anyone with interest in how AI can bring innovation in bioph
 armaceutical and biological manufacturing.\n\nAcademic researchers and univ
 ersity facultyGraduate and undergraduate studentsIndustry professionals and
  entrepreneursGovernment policy makers and bioscience educatorsThis event i
 s planned to focus on the opportunities and challenges in the use of AI too
 ls to improve biomanufacturing workflows and promote a more reliable and ef
 ficient operating paradigm.\n\nSpeakers and Topics\n\nThe symposium will fe
 ature an extraordinary lineup of speakers\, and topics to be addressed may 
 include:\n\nAI-enhanced visual assessment for early viral detectionImplemen
 tation of AI to facilitate decision-making in the quality oversight workflo
 wsThe use of AI to leverage process data in real-time process adjustments a
 nd correctionsTransforming continuous validation with the integration of AI
 Event Highlights\n\nHear from pioneers across academia and industryInteract
 ive panel discussion — Challenges of AI implementation\, technology readine
 ss and regulatory approachesNetworking opportunities — Connect with thought
  leaders\, researchers and manufacturers interested in the use of AI techno
 logyConference Tracks and Topics\n\nTo foster dynamic and diverse discussio
 ns\, the conference is organized into the following thematic tracks:\n\nApp
 lication of AI to improve manufacturing processesAI enhancement of analytic
 al capabilities and release testingIntegration of AI in the quality oversig
 ht processes to improve decision-makingChallenges of AI integration\, imple
 mentation and maintenance in a regulated environmentRegistration Informatio
 n\n\nConference registration will open on Sept. 1\, 2025. Attendance is lim
 ited to the venue capacity.\n\nStandard Registration\n\nNo cost for attenda
 nceParking near NC State’s Hunt Library providedVirtual attendance: A link 
 will be provided prior to the event\, and each session will allow for quest
 ions from virtual attendeesRegistration includes access to keynote sessions
 \, panel discussions\, virtual networking platforms and digital conference 
 materialsFor inquiries regarding registration\, sponsorship or general ques
 tions\, please reach out to Juan Torres at jltorre2@ncsu.edu. Our organizin
 g team is committed to providing timely and helpful support.
DTEND:20260312T220000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025711Z
DTSTART:20260312T120000Z
GEO:35.769292;-78.676638
LOCATION:James B. Hunt Jr. Library\, Duke Energy Hall
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:BTEC Symposium on Applied AI in Biomanufacturing
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51897189723013
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/btec-symposium-on-applied-ai-in-biomanu
 facturing
