BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Training
DESCRIPTION:Join the AI4CommsHub for the Innovative AI Communication Hub Wo
 rkshop\, a two‑part\, immersive learning experience designed to help studen
 ts build practical skills in AI literacy\, ethical evaluation and strategic
  communication.\n\nThe first workshop will be March 13 and is best suited f
 or students newer to AI\, research-focused students and those interested in
  information credibility and ethics. The workshop will introduce participan
 ts to foundational AI concepts\, responsible use practices and communicatio
 n strategies for academic\, industry and research settings. Students will l
 earn how to evaluate AI outputs\, integrate AI into their workflow and appl
 y ethical frameworks to real communication challenges.\n\nWorkshop particip
 ants will:\n\nBuild practical AI and communication skillsParticipate in the
  AI Creator Challenge and poster presentationsCompete for prizes and valuab
 le packages of online training boot camp coursesEarn recognition as an ethi
 cal AI communicatorReceive a certificate of completion upon completing the 
 AI challenge\, poster presentation and surveysCreate portfolio-ready projec
 ts.Network with peers\, faculty and industry-connected mentors.The project 
 is designed to equip students in biological and agricultural engineering te
 chnology\,  biological and agricultural engineering and other STEM discipli
 nes with essential AI literacy\,  ethical communication competencies and ha
 nds-on experience using emerging AI tools\, such as ChatGPT\, Midjourney an
 d domain-specific AI applications in agriculture and engineering. However\,
  this workshop is open to undergraduate and graduate students in STEM\, com
 munication\, design and related fields. Students interested in AI literacy\
 , ethical technology use\, science communication or interdisciplinary colla
 boration will benefit from the program. Prior technical experience with AI 
 tools is not required.\n\nRegistration is required. Early bird registrants 
 will receive a free:\n\nAI learning kit (valued at $50) — includes a custom
  notebook\, a USB drive with AI resources\, a portfolio folder\, worksheets
  and collaboration toolsAI training textbook (valued at $50) — a hands-on g
 uide for AI literacy\, ethical awareness and real-world application skillsL
 unch
DTEND:20260313T203000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025711Z
DTSTART:20260313T150000Z
