BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Training
DESCRIPTION:Burnout is a growing concern for many employers\, as it can imp
 act morale\, employee retention\, work productivity and more. Join Learning
  and Organizational Development (L&OD) for a training session that will int
 roduce leaders to strategies that can help them prevent burnout from impact
 ing the workforce. This training will help you:\n\nIdentify factors that in
 crease the likelihood that burnout will become a problemIdentify signals th
 at indicate an employee may be starting to feel burnt outCreate a work envi
 ronment that makes burnout less likelyInitiate productive conversations wit
 h employees who are showing signs of burnoutThe workshop is part of L&OD's 
 Leadership Education and Development (LEAD) program. LEAD Events are opport
 unities to learn or refresh skills to help you grow your career.
DTEND:20260323T070000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025711Z
DTSTART:20260323T060000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:LEAD Event: Preventing Employee Burnout
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52055675916181
