BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Films
DESCRIPTION:The Global Film Series will present a screening of Okko’s Inn.\
 n\nAfter losing her parents in a car accident\, Okko goes to live in the co
 untryside with her grandmother\, who runs a traditional Japanese inn built 
 on top of an ancient spring said to have healing waters. While she goes abo
 ut her chores and prepares to become the inn’s next caretaker\, Okko discov
 ers some spirits live there that only she can see — not scary ones but welc
 oming ghosts who keep her company\, play games and help her navigate her ne
 w environment. The inn’s motto is that it welcomes all and will reject none
 \, and this is soon put to the test as a string of new guests challenge Okk
 o’s ability to be a gracious host. But ultimately\, Okko discovers that ded
 icating herself to others becomes the key to taking care of herself.\n\nThe
  film's runtime is 1 hour\, 34 minutes. The movie is in Japanese with Engli
 sh subtitles. \n\nThe Global Film Series is a collaboration between the NC 
 State University Libraries and NC State’s Office of Global Engagement. This
  screening is in partnership with NC State’s Women’s Center in celebration 
 of Women’s History Month.
DTEND:20260325T003000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025711Z
DTSTART:20260324T223000Z
GEO:35.769292;-78.676638
LOCATION:James B. Hunt Jr. Library\, Auditorium
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Global Film Series: Okko’s Inn 
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51751171656820
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/global-film-series-okkos-inn-japan
END:VEVENT
