BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Lectures and Talks
DESCRIPTION:You might have great work - but is your portfolio actually work
 ing for you? Many talented creatives miss opportunities not because of skil
 l\, but because their portfolio doesn’t communicate their potential effecti
 vely. In this workshop\, you’ll learn: ✅ What recruiters look for in a port
 folio and how to make yours stand out✅ How to frame your work to create a s
 trong and cohesive presentation✅ Why showcasing a range of skills is import
 ant and how to do it effectively✅ When and how to include spec work to stre
 ngthen your portfolio About the Speaker: Kevin is a Creative Director out o
 f Dallas\, TX with over a decade of experience working for brands like Sams
 ung\, Audi\, FedEx Office\, and Krispy Kreme. He has won numerous National 
 Addys\, has been published in Graphis Design and Poster Annuals\, and is li
 sted among Lurzer's Int'l Archives 200 Best Illustrators Worldwide. This ev
 ent is brought to you by ArtBound Initiative. ArtBound Initiative connects 
 students and recent graduates with key players in the creative industry in 
 New York\, Chicago\, Los Angeles\, Miami\, Austin\, Berlin\, Melbourne\, Sy
 dney & Virtual. The program includes: guaranteed internship\, internship co
 aching curriculum\, travel support (housing\, visa & insurance)\, and event
 s.
DTEND:20260326T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025711Z
DTSTART:20260326T000000Z
LOCATION:
