DESCRIPTION:Join the NC State Entrepreneurship Clinic for a social hour tha
 t will celebrate the eClinic’s move to the Albright Entrepreneurship Garage
  on Centennial Campus.\n\nThe eClinic is supported by the Poole College of 
 Management and works as an integral part of the NC State Innovation and Ent
 repreneurship portfolio. This transition positions our students\, founders 
 and partners at the center of one of the most dynamic ecosystems in the reg
 ion — where research\, startups and corporate innovators intersect daily.\n
 \nThe social hour will include a toast to Chip and Lyn Andrews for their le
 adership and vision of the Andrews Launch Accelerator and will spotlight th
 e opportunities the move will create.\n\nStronger partnerships with on-camp
 us departments and research centersDeeper engagement with Centennial Campus
  companiesExpanded collaboration across our vibrant startup ecosystem.More 
 hands-on\, high-impact learning experiences for students.By embedding the E
 ntrepreneurship Clinic within the Entrepreneurship Garage\, we are accelera
 ting our program by connecting talent\, ideas and industry to transform bol
 d concepts into scalable ventures.
