BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:
DESCRIPTION:Please join us for a guest lecture by Kholisil Dhilwayo. \n\nKh
 olisile Dhliwayo\n\nKholisile Dhliwayo is an architect\, artist\, and curat
 or who specializes in culturally responsive\, context-driven design. His wo
 rks includes Brooklyn Bronzes\, a permanent installation at the Museum of C
 ontemporary African Diasporan Arts honoring Black Brooklynites\, and Black 
 Diasporas\, a geolocated oral narrative archive and exhibition about Black 
 life in Tkaronto-Toronto\, Naarm-Melbourne\, Boorloo-Perth\, and Warrane-Sy
 dney.\n\nHe has also contributed to various civic projects\, including the 
 Canadian Senate\, Javits Center\, and David Geffen Hall. A Harvard Kennedy 
 School Social Innovation Change Initiative fellow and Harvard GSD graduate\
 , his interdisciplinary approach is relational and collaborative\, engaging
  art\, technology\, and culture as tools to make architecture\, interiors\,
  and installations that are reflective of place\, people\, and culture.
DTEND:20260326T220000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025711Z
DTSTART:20260326T210000Z
GEO:35.784712;-78.665536
LOCATION:Kamphoefner Hall\, Burns Auditorium
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Design Studies Lecture: Kholisile Dhliwayo\, Black Diasporas
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52267218111074
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/kholisile-dhliwayo-black-diasporas
END:VEVENT
