BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Community Events,Performances,Student Life
DESCRIPTION:The State Dance Company will present a multimedia dance concert
  and community engagement project inspired by Isabel Allende’s What the Win
 d Remembers and other works of literature and art that illuminate refugee e
 xperiences. Allende’s novel follows two child refugees who are separated fr
 om their parents while seeking safety in a new country. Inspired by the nov
 el and broader artistic and historical narratives\, the concert will explor
 e themes of displacement\, resilience and hope and incorporate stories from
  local refugee communities.\n\nChoreography is by director Tara Z. Mullins\
 , Tracey Durbin\, dance faculty member Amy Love Beasley and Francine E. Ott
 .\n\nThis performance is made possible by an arts and science Grant from th
 e Data Science and AI Academy\, along with the Office of Interdisciplinary 
 Programs and Arts NC State.\n\nTickets go on sale Monday\, Feb. 16.
DTEND:20260327T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025711Z
DTSTART:20260326T230000Z
GEO:35.784114;-78.671321
LOCATION:Talley Student Union\, Stewart Theatre
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:State Dance Company Concert
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51905088576906
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/state-dance-company-concert
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Lectures and Talks
DESCRIPTION:Thinking about becoming a Creative Director? Join us for a cand
 id Insider Talk with Holly Karlsson\, a seasoned creative leader with 20+ y
 ears of experience crafting campaigns for Heineken\, Coca-Cola\, Disney\, N
 ike\, Sony\, and Unilever. Hear what it’s really like to lead creative team
 s\, make big-picture decisions\, and bring ideas to life — and get practica
 l advice for aspiring Creative Directors looking to build the skills\, mind
 set\, and portfolio that make a future leader stand out.\n\nWhat you’ll lea
 rn:\n\n✅ A realistic day-to-day view as a Creative Director\n\n✅ How to bui
 ld the skills and mindset that help juniors stand out\n\n✅ Steps you can ta
 ke now to start moving toward a creative leadership career\n\nAbout the Spe
 aker: Holly Karlsson is Creative Director at Bulletproof\, an independent s
 trategic brand design agency with studios in London\, New York\, Singapore\
 , Amsterdam\, Sydney and Shanghai. Having worked in the industry for over 2
 0 years\, Holly has created striking campaigns for the likes of Heineken\, 
 Coca-Cola\, Disney\, Nike\, Sony and Unilever. This event is brought to you
  by ArtBound Initiative. ArtBound Initiative connects students and recent g
 raduates with key players in the creative industry in New York\, Chicago\, 
 Los Angeles\, Miami\, Austin\, Berlin\, Melbourne\, Sydney & Virtual. The p
 rogram includes: guaranteed internship\, internship coaching curriculum\, t
 ravel support (housing\, visa & insurance)\, and events.
DTEND:20260327T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025711Z
DTSTART:20260327T000000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Insider Talk: What It’s Really Like to Be a Creative Director
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52382960951831
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/insider-talk-holly-karlsson
END:VEVENT
