BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Information Session
DESCRIPTION:Are you a science communicator\, interested in the science comm
 unication field or want to learn about science communication skills? Do you
  want to share your expertise in communicating science or share research wi
 th new audiences? Are you curious about how the arts can amplify your scien
 ce research? Are you an artist who works at the intersection of art and sci
 ence and wants to find science research partners for mutually rewarding art
 s-integrated research opportunities?\n\nScience communication is a rich fie
 ld made up of researchers and practitioners who understand that science res
 earch needs to be thoughtfully contextualized for increased impact on the p
 ublic good. Join Arts NC State\, the Office of Research and Innovation and 
 the College of Sciences for a meeting at the Gregg Museum of Art & Design t
 o share your expertise or learn about communicating science at NC State. Du
 ring the meeting\, you can propose ideas and topics for a series of Communi
 cating Science workshops that will be held during the 2026-2027 academic ye
 ar. We’d love for you to participate.
DTEND:20260330T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025712Z
DTSTART:20260330T200000Z
GEO:35.784762;-78.661636
LOCATION:Gregg Museum of Art & Design
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Communicating Science Interest Kickoff Meeting
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52258126357463
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/communicating-science-interest-kickoff-
 meeting
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Lectures and Talks
DESCRIPTION:Please join the College of Design for the spring 2026 architect
 ure lecture series. \n\nSusan Rodriguez\, Susan T. Rodriguez | Architecture
  · Design\n\nSusan T Rodriguez | Architecture · Design was founded in 2017\
 , combining more than thirty years of design leadership with a passionate b
 elief in the power of architecture to affect change and improve the quality
  of life for all. The studio\, a New York City certified Women-Owned Busine
 ss Enterprise and federally certified Women-Owned Small Business\, builds u
 pon an award-winning body of work recognized internationally for design exc
 ellence and contributing to the vitality of cities\, landscapes and the com
 munities and institutions it serves. Central to the practice is an emphasis
  on addressing pressing issues in contemporary society through design that 
 promotes the wellbeing of communities and the long-term sustainability of t
 he environment.  \n\nDesigning at the intersection of architecture and the 
 public realm\, the studio distills the essence of cultures and communities 
 through work that ranges in scale and type\, from interventions in historic
  precincts to new large-scale monumental buildings. To each project\, STR |
  A·D brings an attitude about design that connects people to place and to e
 ach other through an architecture of interpretation. The work is inspired b
 y the confluence of history\, site\, program and the relationship of interi
 or and exterior space. Whether rural landscape\, campus setting or a dense 
 urban context\, STR | A·D seeks to create an architecture that is fused wit
 h its surroundings and the natural world.
DTEND:20260330T230000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025712Z
DTSTART:20260330T213000Z
GEO:35.784712;-78.665536
LOCATION:Kamphoefner Hall\, Burns Auditorium
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Architecture Lecture: Susan Rodriguez\, Susan T. Rodriguez | Archit
 ecture · Design
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51888789012671
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/architecture-lecture-susan-rodriguez
END:VEVENT
