BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Lectures and Talks,Films
DESCRIPTION:Globally\, sand tiger shark populations have experienced signif
 icant declines\, and some populations are now considered critically endange
 red. The North Carolina Aquariums are working to expand our understanding o
 f this shark’s ecology\, behavior and habitat use by working with scientist
 s and partner organizations to conduct sand tiger shark research. Come lear
 n how Spot A Shark USA engages NC State undergraduate students\, scientists
 \, scuba divers and underwater photographers in sand tiger shark research.\
 n\nThis program will feature a screening of the documentary film\, Sharks i
 n a Changing Sea: Stories from the Depths and the People Who Know Them\, fo
 llowed by Q&A and a discussion of student opportunities at the Center for M
 arine Sciences and Technology. Representatives from the NC State Marine Sci
 ence Club and the Raleigh Diving Club will also share information.\n\nBe su
 re to also check out the Swimming With Sharks immersive exhibit in the Cyma
  Rubin Visualization Gallery.
DTEND:20260401T213000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025712Z
DTSTART:20260401T203000Z
GEO:35.787562;-78.669711
LOCATION:D.H. Hill Jr. Library\, Fishbowl Forum
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Sharks in a Changing Sea
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51760067657847
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/sharks-in-a-changing-sea
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Lectures and Talks
DESCRIPTION:Please join the College of Design for the spring 2026 landscape
  architecture lecture series. \n\nLarry Weaner\, Principal and Founder\, LW
 LA\n\n \n\nLarry Weaner traces his success to a lifetime of observing natur
 e.  As a child\, he observed the wild vegetation along the railroad tracks 
 behind his childhood Philadelphia home.  His observations over the ensuing 
 40 years inform an array of influential projects\, from small residential p
 roperties to major public spaces.\n\nLarry founded LWLA in 1982 after recei
 ving his Associates Degree in Ornamental Horticulture from the Pennsylvania
  College of Technology and has gone on to design prestigious public and pri
 vate landscapes. Larry’s book\, Garden Revolution: How Our Landscapes Can B
 e a Source of Environmental Change (Timber Press\, 2016)\, is a literary re
 flection on his life’s work and foundational ecological principles.  It rec
 eived the American Horticultural Society Book Award in 2017.
DTEND:20260401T233000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025712Z
DTSTART:20260401T220000Z
GEO:35.784712;-78.665536
LOCATION:Kamphoefner Hall\, Burns Auditorium
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Landscape Architecture Lecture: Larry Weaner\, LWLA
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51897511509700
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/landscape-architecture-lecture-larry-we
 aner
END:VEVENT
