DESCRIPTION:Wolfpack Pictures will screen Pan's Labyrinth as part of its Fi
 lm Genres series. In 1944 in Spain\, a girl is sent to live with her ruthle
 ss stepfather. During the night\, she meets a faun who tells her she is a p
 rincess\, but she must prove her royalty by surviving three gruesome tasks.
 \n\nThis free event is open to the public. Nora Kilcup\, who is earning a M
 aster of Arts in English with a concentration in film studies\, will introd
 uce the movie and lead a talk-back session after the screening.\n\nWolfpack
  Pictures is a film collective run by graduate students in the Department o
 f English and the Ph.D. Program in Communication\, Rhetoric and Digital Med
 ia. If you have questions about the screening\, contact faculty sponsor Joh
 n Stadler.
