BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Lectures and Talks
DESCRIPTION:Join us for the spring 2026 graphic design lecture series. \n\n
 Dana Gierdowski\n\nDana is a senior research leader specializing in human-c
 entered research\, accessibility\, and inclusive product design. With deep 
 expertise in mixed-methods research and research operations\, she transform
 s human stories into strategic insights that guide product vision\, shape i
 nnovation pipelines\, and help executive teams make confident\, evidence-ba
 sed decisions.\n\nDana currently serves as Senior Manager of User Experienc
 e Design\, Research & Insights at Lenovo\, where she leads global research 
 initiatives across hardware\, software\, AR/VR\, AI\, and next-generation P
 C design. She builds and develops high-performing research teams\, establis
 hes scalable research operations\, and delivers insights that directly infl
 uence product strategy at a global scale—including accessibility advancemen
 ts recognized with multiple Lenovo impact awards.
DTEND:20260407T213000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025712Z
DTSTART:20260407T203000Z
