DESCRIPTION:Step into the world of immersive learning at the Extended Reali
 ty (XR) Showcase\, happening Wednesday\, April 8\, from 11 a.m. to 1 p.m.\,
  in the D.H. Hill Library Gaming and VR Studio. The XR Showcase is hosted b
 y DELTA in collaboration with the NC State Libraries.\n\nDesigned like a ha
 nds-on science fair\, this open-house-style event invites NC State faculty 
 and staff to explore how immersive technologies\, such as virtual and augme
 nted reality\, are transforming teaching and learning. You’ll have the chan
 ce to experience a range of XR tools\, participate in live demonstrations a
 nd learn how to get started with XR resources and spaces available through 
 DELTA and the Libraries. Instructors who are already integrating XR into th
 eir courses will also be there to share their work and ideas with you. Join
  us for the XR Showcase to get inspired\, connected and see what’s possible
  with XR technology.
