DESCRIPTION:The Importance of Being Earnest\, a Trivial Comedy for Serious 
 People\, is Oscar Wilde’s comedic play\, which satirizes the conventions an
 d manners of the late 19th century. Best friends Jack and Algernon each ado
 pt fictional identities to escape social obligations. The plot unfolds with
  mistaken identities\, romantic entanglements\, clever wordplay and humorou
 s social commentary.\n\nThe play's director is Danica Jenelle Jackson.
