BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Performances
DESCRIPTION:The Classics Club invites you to attend a performance by Chicag
 o-based singer-songwriter Joe Goodkin on Thursday\, April 9\, at 7:45 p.m. 
 at Talley Student Union. Goodkin\, who earned a Bachelor's of Arts in Class
 ics at the University of Wisconsin-Madison\, created The Blues of Achilles\
 , a musical adaptation of The Iliad\, an epic poem by Greek poet Homer. The
  Blues of Achilles is a set of 17 original songs. It tells the story of The
  Iliad through the eyes of its characters: Achilles\, Patroclus\, Briseis\,
  Helen\, Priam and more. The performance evokes the original oral tradition
  of epic bards that stretches back millennia and frames the poem musically 
 and narratively for modern audiences.\n\nThe performance will conclude at 9
  p.m. A Q&A session will follow. Registration is required to attend.\n\nRef
 reshments will be available.
DTEND:20260410T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025712Z
DTSTART:20260409T234500Z
GEO:35.784114;-78.671321
