BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Lectures and Talks
DESCRIPTION:Join us to learn about the Endangerment Finding and what its re
 scission means (and doesn’t mean) for future GHG emissions.\n\nIn February\
 , EPA rescinded its own legal authority to regulate greenhouse gas emission
 s under the Clean Air Act\, known as the Endangerment Finding. This action 
 may have lasting implications for EPA’s future ability to regulate the GHGs
  that cause climate change. Hear more about the Finding\, the implications 
 of its rescission\, and what might be next for GHG emissions from speaker\,
  Andy Miller.\n\nAndy Miller is CaSA's Practitioner-in-Residence (PIR) and 
 an original author of the Endangerment Finding who spent 30 years working f
 or the EPA.\n\nPlease register using NC State email address.
DTEND:20260410T170000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025712Z
DTSTART:20260410T160000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Lunch and Learn with Andy Miller: EPA Endangerment Finding
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52428535157785
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/lunch-and-learn-with-andy-miller-epa-en
 dangerment-finding
