BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Films
DESCRIPTION:Join the Global Film Series\, a collaboration between the NC St
 ate University Libraries and NC State’s Office of Global Engagement\, for a
  screening of On Becoming a Guinea Fowl.\n\nOn an empty road in the middle 
 of the night\, Shula stumbles across the body of her uncle. As funeral proc
 eedings begin\, Shula and her cousins bring to light the buried secrets of 
 their middle-class Zambian family. \n\nThe movie runtime is 1 hour\, 39 min
 utes. The film is in English and Bemba with English subtitles. \n\nDr. Hadd
 y Njie\, associate teaching professor in International Studies at NC State\
 , will introduce the film. \n\nThe Global Film Series is a collaboration be
 tween the NC State University Libraries and NC State’s Office of Global Eng
 agement. This screening is in partnership with the NC State Department of I
 nternational Studies and Africana Studies.
DTEND:20260415T003000Z
