BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Lectures and Talks
DESCRIPTION:The Department of Mathematics invites you to the annual Kwangil
  Koh Lecture. This year's speakers distinguished speaker is Robert L. Bryan
 t\, renowned mathematician and former president of the American Mathematica
 l Society. Bryant is known for his groundbreaking work in differential geom
 etry and its applications across science and technology.\n\nHis lecture\, “
 Parking Cars\, Rolling Balls and Falling Cats: The Concept of Holonomy\,” w
 ill explore how studying motion with constraints that occur in everyday lif
 e leads to a deeper understanding of the relationship between curvature and
  geometry.\n\nThe lecture will be preceded by a reception at 5 p.m.
DTSTAMP:20260326T025712Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260416
GEO:35.784748;-78.666662
LOCATION:SAS Hall\, 2203
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Kwangil Koh Lecture 
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52436056172064
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/kwangil-koh-lecture
END:VEVENT
