BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Community Events
DESCRIPTION:NC State’s Terrain Dance Project will present Themes of Gatheri
 ng\, a collection of new site-specific choreographic works at The Corner on
  Centennial Campus at 2 p.m. April 17 and 7 p.m. April 18. The Terrain Danc
 e Project is a site-specific dance company dedicated to the creation and pe
 rformance of choreographed and improvised dance works in nontraditional spa
 ces\, including dance film projects.\n\nThis interdisciplinary performance 
 investigates The Corner as a site of gathering and identity\, featuring liv
 e musicians and choreography by co-director Amy Love Beasley\, guest artist
 s Jill Guyton Nee and Anabelle Scarborough and NC State senior Annabelle Sh
 arp. Select works explore the intersection of dance and science\, inspired 
 by work by NC State's Gage Lab and the North Carolina Sweetpotato Commissio
 n. This project is supported by an arts and science grant from the Office o
 f Interdisciplinary Programs and Arts NC State.\n\nIn case of inclement wea
 ther on the scheduled performance dates\, the performances will take place 
 April 19 at 2 and 7 p.m.
DTEND:20260419T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025712Z
DTSTART:20260418T230000Z
GEO:35.771604;-78.676356
LOCATION:The Corner
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Terrain Dance Project Concert: Themes of Gathering
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52027778954369
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/terrain-dance-project-concert-themes-of
 -gathering
END:VEVENT
