BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Community Events,Tours and Open Houses
DESCRIPTION:Tour the Constructed Facilities Lab\, a civil engineering parad
 ise where concrete bends\, metal freezes and earthquakes are an everyday oc
 currence. You'll be guided by CFL researchers who can show you all of their
  coolest toys and tell you about the importance of their research and its i
 mpact on the world.\nThis is an educational experience\, but it is also an 
 incredibly entertaining peek into one of the most hands-on and immediately 
 recognizable research experiences on campus. Their machines might be compli
 cated\, but when you get to watch a decommissioned bridge pillar break unde
 r a shake test\, it is as fascinating to watch as it is to instantly unders
 tand why it matters.\nSlots are limited\, so please register to attend the 
 tour.
DTEND:20260420T160000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025712Z
DTSTART:20260420T150000Z
GEO:35.768715;-78.67954
LOCATION:Constructed Facilities Lab\, Main Entrance
SEQUENCE:0
