BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Community Events
DESCRIPTION:Art2Wear continues its traditions by pushing fashion and form i
 n its 2026 production: Symbiosis. Symbiosis works to integrate designers' u
 nderstanding of interactions\, push and pulls\, constraints and appendages.
  Whether ancient interactions between humanity and nature or emerging engag
 ements with technologies\, this year explores polarities in interactions to
  showcase the impact of forces and the world’s curation when things come to
 gether.\n\nArt2Wear will be showcased at the Gregg Museum of Art & Design. 
 \n\nThis year\, there are multiple showtimes for Art2Wear:\n\n7-9 pm on Apr
 il 234-6 pm on April 247-9 pm on April 24What is Art2Wear?\n\nArt2WearTM (A
 2W) is an educational event where students gain experience by coordinating 
 and producing an annual wearable art production. Young designers are challe
 nged to imagine\, create\, and inspire by expressing their point of view th
 rough wearable art. This highly anticipated show fuses the talents of sever
 al departments in the College of Design and beyond\, exposing student desig
 ners to the broader field of wearable art\, digital media production\, and 
 fashion. A2W attracts attendees from all over the Triangle by encouraging p
 articipation through engaging the student body\, the Raleigh community\, an
 d the broader design industry.
