BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Lectures and Talks
DESCRIPTION:Ever wondered what it's like having a career designing exhibiti
 ons\, museums\, and cultural experiences? Join us with Gretchen Coss to lea
 rn how experience design teams bring stories to life across museums\, cultu
 ral institutions\, and public spaces. What you’ll learn:✅ What a career in 
 experience design can look like✅ The skills and projects that help juniors 
 stand out✅ Concrete steps you can take now to start building relevant exper
 ience About the Speaker: Gretchen is a visionary leader\, educator\, and de
 signer with over thirty-five years of experience in brand management\, expe
 rience design\, and placemaking. She is currently the Vice President of Str
 ategic Partnerships at G&A Design\, a design firm specializing in experient
 ial design that is based in New York. This event is brought to you by ArtBo
 und Initiative. ArtBound Initiative connects students and recent graduates 
 with key players in the creative industry in New York\, Chicago\, Los Angel
 es\, Miami\, Austin\, Berlin\, Melbourne\, Sydney & Virtual. The program in
 cludes: guaranteed internship\, internship coaching curriculum\, travel sup
 port (housing\, visa & insurance)\, and events.
DTEND:20260424T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025712Z
DTSTART:20260424T000000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
