BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Community Events
DESCRIPTION:Come volunteer and celebrate Earth Month by spending a few hour
 s beautifying Lake Raleigh\, a 75-acre lake amid a 96-acre protected forest
 \, April 24. Earth Day is April 22.\n\nVolunteer tasks will include collect
 ing litter along greenway trails\, natural trails and Lake Raleigh.\n\nTrai
 ning and volunteering: All volunteers must attend a safety training session
  at 10 a.m. You can decide how long to volunteer. The clean-up effort will 
 conclude by noon.\n\nWhere to join us and park: You can join the volunteer 
 effort at either of the following locations:\n\nThe Lake Raleigh fishing pi
 er: If you plan to walk or ride a bike or the bus from campus\, consider me
 eting us at the fishing pier. Paid parking is available at the Poulton park
 ing lot on Partners Way.The Park Alumni Center: The center's address is 245
 0 Alumni Drive in Raleigh\, and parking there is free.What to bring: Volunt
 eers must wear close-toed shoes. Please bring water in a reusable water bot
 tle so you can stay hydrated. All other materials and supplies\, such as gl
 oves\, will be provided.\n\nIf you have questions about the clean-up effort
 \, send an email to sustainability@ncsu.edu.
DTEND:20260424T160000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025712Z
DTSTART:20260424T140000Z
GEO:35.767879;-78.677586
LOCATION:Lake Raleigh
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:NC State Earth Day Cleanup
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51328310281090
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/nc_state_earth_day_clean_up
