BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Community Events
DESCRIPTION:Caring for plants is both an art and a science — part intuition
 \, part know-how. Every gardener\, from beginner to expert\, faces the same
  essential questions: When should I prune? How much should I water? What’s 
 the best way to plant\, fertilize or repot? In this class\, Bryce Lane will
  bring decades of horticultural expertise to demystify these everyday tasks
 \, showing you not just what to do but why it works.\n\nOver eight weeks\, 
 you’ll explore the fundamental practices that keep gardens thriving\, learn
 ing how to perform each one with confidence and purpose. You’ll uncover the
  science behind good technique — understanding how soil\, water\, nutrients
  and plant biology interact — while also developing the practical judgment 
 that comes only with experience.\n\nEach session will focus on one key aspe
 ct of plant care\, building a complete toolkit for growing healthier\, more
  resilient plants in any garden setting.
DTEND:20260428T003000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025712Z
DTSTART:20260427T223000Z
GEO:35.794251;-78.699671
LOCATION:JC Raulston Arboretum
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:The Art and Science of Plant Care
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52072165587831
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/the-art-and-science-of-plant-care
END:VEVENT
