BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Community Events,Student Life,De-Stress Fest
DESCRIPTION:Come practice mindfulness and grounding on a guided soundscape 
 walk along the Rocky Branch trail. The sounds around us make up our soundsc
 ape and have a profound effect on our mental\, physical and cognitive well-
 being. Your guide will share research findings on how noticing sounds aroun
 d you can support wellness and help you engage with bird and insect calls. 
 All participants will have the option to contribute to Sound Around Town\, 
 a participatory science project led by Caren Cooper that aims to further ou
 r understanding of how sound relates to wellness.\n\nWe will meet at the Ca
 mpus Health Center entrance that faces the Rocky Branch Trail. Please bring
  water\, a hat and sunglasses and dress in comfortable clothing.
DTEND:20260429T143000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025713Z
DTSTART:20260429T133000Z
GEO:35.784684;-78.675176
LOCATION:Campus Health
SEQUENCE:0
