BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Community Events,Student Life
DESCRIPTION:Department of Electrical and Computer Engineering students will
  present research documenting the maintenance challenges of the iconic Voll
 is Simpson Whirligig Park in Wilson at the Greg Museum of Art & Design.\n\n
 The presentation schedule is below. Choose the session that fits your sched
 ule. Both sessions will offer the same educational content\n\n1-1:30 p.m. (
 Student project presentations)Students will present their research projecti
 ons\, using a live TV feed from Whirligig Park to illustrate how conservati
 on challenges\, such as monitoring wear or predicting failures\, directly i
 nform their research and solutions.\n\n1:30-1:45 p.m. (Q&A session)Particip
 ants can inquire about students’ methods\, their findings and the engineeri
 ng principles applied to conversation.\n\n1:45-2 p.m. (Guided tour of the V
 ollis Simpson Whirligig by the Gregg Museum)A member of the Gregg Museum ed
 ucation team will lead attendees outside for a focused tour of Vollis Simps
 on’s whirligig\, Crossroads\, on the front lawn\, connecting the presented 
 research to the physical kinetic sculpture.\n\nSession 2: 2-3 p.m.\n\n2-2:3
 0 p.m. (repeat of Session 1 presentations)2:30-2:45 p.m. (Q&A session)2:45-
 3 p.m. (repeat of Session 1 guided tour)
DTEND:20260508T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025713Z
DTSTART:20260508T170000Z
GEO:35.784762;-78.661636
LOCATION:Gregg Museum of Art & Design\, Front Lawn
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:A Dive Into the Vollis Simpson Whirligigs
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51949208112579
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/engineering-conservation-a-dive-into-th
 e-vollis-simpson-whirligigs
END:VEVENT
