BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Training
DESCRIPTION:DELTA-Con\, now in its ninth year\, is NC State’s annual unconf
 erence that brings together attendees from NC State University and local hi
 gher education institutions. Faculty\, staff and teaching assistants are we
 lcome to attend this discussion-based event to share their insights into hi
 gher education. DELTA-Con is a great way for you to network with your peers
  and discover the latest in academic technology and innovation.\n\nHow Does
  DELTA-Con Work?\n\nAs a participant\, you will create sessions collaborati
 vely with other attendees. After registering\, you can add your ideas to a 
 big board of possible topics that we will continue building at DELTA-Con. O
 n the day of the event\, we will finalize a schedule based on participant i
 nterest. Each session will then be facilitated by a DELTA staff member but 
 led by the participants in the room\, who will share best practices\, discu
 ss challenges\, work through ideas and more. We will also keep collaborativ
 e notes so you have a takeaway from each session.\n\nSample Past Topics\n\n
 Innovative uses of AI in teaching and assessment.Increasing student engagem
 ent in online courses.Inclusive teaching practicesAlternative assessments
DTEND:20260512T173000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025713Z
DTSTART:20260512T123000Z
GEO:35.769292;-78.676638
LOCATION:James B. Hunt Jr. Library\, IEI
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:DELTA-Con 2026
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52261699781641
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/delta-con-2026-7683
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Community Events,Student Life,Tours and Open Houses
DESCRIPTION:Please join us on a monthly basis for a walk through the Lake R
 aleigh Woods\, one of NC State's hidden gems and Hallowed Spaces. The hike 
 is about 1.5 miles. Below are a few things to remember for the hike:\n\nMak
 e sure to park in the northwest corner of the Park Alumni Center parking lo
 t a little before 9 a.m. for a brief safety conversation. Parking is free f
 or everyone. Wear closed-toed shoes and bring a water bottle.Check the weat
 her forecast and wear weather-appropriate clothing on the hike.Restrooms ar
 e available in the Alumni Center. There are no facilities on the trail.The 
 hike will last approximately 90 minutes but could be a little shorter depen
 ding on the group's pace. Space is limited for each hike. Be sure to regist
 er.\n\nLake Raleigh Woods Hikes are recognized as a Campus Nature Rx Progra
 m\, an international movement built around encouraging universities and the
 ir communities to engage with the physical and mental health benefits of be
 ing in nature.
DTEND:20260512T143000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025713Z
DTSTART:20260512T130000Z
GEO:35.767879;-78.677586
LOCATION:Lake Raleigh
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Lake Raleigh Woods Hike
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51435730878398
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/lake-raleigh-woods-hike
END:VEVENT
