BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:
DESCRIPTION:Join the Campus Writing and Speaking Program (CWSP) on Monday\,
  Oct. 20\, for NC State Writes\, a campuswide celebration of the National D
 ay on Writing. From 9 a.m. to 2 p.m.\, stop by our pop-up writing stations 
 at the D.H. Hill Jr. Library and Talley Student Union to:\n\nShare your #Wh
 yIWrite storyAdd a line to our collaborative Wolfpack poemTry quick-write p
 rompts to spark creativityPick up free CWSP swagAt 12:30 p.m.\, join NC Sta
 te Writes Together for a campuswide writing pause connecting students\, fac
 ulty and staff through shared reflection and creativity. For 10 minutes\, w
 e'll all respond to this question: "What does being part of the Wolfpack me
 an to you?"\n\nIf you can’t join us in person\, participate on social media
  by posting your own #WhyIWrite story with #WolfpackWrites.\n\nAll are welc
 ome to participate — because at NC State\, we all write.
DTEND:20261020T180000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T025713Z
DTSTART:20261020T130000Z
GEO:35.784114;-78.671321
LOCATION:Talley Student Union
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:NC State Writes: Celebrating the National Day on Writing
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_50966564247672
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/nc-state-writes-celebrating-the-nationa
 l-day-on-writing
END:VEVENT
